Claude d'Aspremont Lynden is a Belgian economist and professor at the Universite Catholique de Louvain, Center for Operations Research and Econometrics (CORE), and Département des sciences économiques (ECON). He obtained a Ph.D. (Dissertation on decision sciences) at the Graduate School of Business, Stanford University (United States) in 1973. His research interest is on mathematical economics, social choice theory, and industrial organization. In 1995, he was awarded the Francqui Prize on Human Sciences.
